      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/35/13",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ رَهَنَ رَهْناً إِلَى وَقْتٍ ثُمَّ غَابَ هَلْ لَهُ وَقْتٌ يُبَاعُ فِيهِ رَهْنُهُ فَقَالَ \"لاَ حَتَّى يَجِيءَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4106 - Al-Qasim ibn Sulaiman narrated from Ubayd ibn Zurara, who reported from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who pledged a security (rahn) for a specified time and then disappeared, should there be a time set to sell his pledge?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"No, it should not be sold until he returns.\""
        ]
      }
    },
